The paper deals with sublinear algorithms for the vertex coloring problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of graph streaming, sublinear time, and massively parallel computation (MPC) algorithms, which are all subfields of computer science that deal with efficient computation on large datasets and fall under the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), distributed computing (cs.DC), and algorithms (cs.AL).
